{"coursehistories": {"path": "/coursehistories/4708"}, "description": "The objective of this course is to provide students with a solid technical foundation for developing, animating and controlling articulated systems used in interactive computer games, physical simulations and high-end animation applications. The course balances theory with practice by \"looking under the hood\" of a number of popular commercial animation packages and examines the technologies and techniques used from both a computer science and engineering perspective. Topics covered include: geometric coordinate systems and transformations; quaternions; parametric curves and surfaces; forward and inverse kinematics; dynamic systems and control; computer simulation; keyframe, motion capture and procedural animation; behavior-based animation and control; facial animation; smart characters and intelligent agents. \n\n", "semester": "2008A", "name": "SPECIAL TOPICS: Computer Vision", "reviews": {"path": "/courses/19936/reviews", "values": [{"ratings": {"rAmountLearned": "3.63", "rDifficulty": "2.50", "rStimulateInterest": "3.88", "rRecommendMajor": "3.38", "rCourseQuality": "3.75", "rWorkRequired": "2.75", "rInstructorAccess": "3.75", "rReadingsValue": "3.33", "rRecommendNonMajor": "2.13", "rCommAbility": "3.75", "rInstructorQuality": "3.75"}, "section": {"name": "SPECIAL TOPICS: Computer Vision", "sectionnum": "001", "primary_alias": "CIS-399-001", "path": "/courses/19936/sections/001", "id": "19936-001", "aliases": ["CIS-399-001"]}, "comments": "", "num_students": 8, "path": "/courses/19936/sections/001/reviews/2074-JIANBO-SHI", "instructor": {"path": "/instructors/2074-JIANBO-SHI", "first_name": "JIANBO", "last_name": "SHI", "id": "2074-JIANBO-SHI", "name": "JIANBO SHI"}, "num_reviewers": 8, "id": "19936-001-2074-JIANBO-SHI"}, {"ratings": {"rAmountLearned": "2.89", "rDifficulty": "2.06", "rStimulateInterest": "2.94", "rRecommendMajor": "3.06", "rCourseQuality": "2.78", "rWorkRequired": "1.94", "r